<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5464" target="_blank">SCP-5464</a> - The Responsibility We Bear - [+110]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;SCP-5464 will enter its activation phase, manifesting its anomalous traits at the inception of an event of historical or political significance to Poland. In this phase, SCP-5464 will demanifest from its current location and will manifest in a place of significance to the inciting event, becoming an ongoing active participant.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This is easily the dumbest thing I have so far written<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-4" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-4')">4</a></sup>. It started off as an inside joke between <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/veralta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6030962); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6030962&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609776161" alt="Veralta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6030962)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/veralta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6030962); return false;">Veralta</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jakob17" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5884163); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5884163&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609776161" alt="Jakob17" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5884163)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jakob17" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5884163); return false;">Jakob17</a></span>, and myself on the SCPD Discord Server, and whilst the stupidity of it was beyond anything I've ever read, I genuinely couldn't resist the urge to write it. The article blew up into +40 within the first day, being my first thing to get into the &quot;big numbers&quot;.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-0000-ex" target="_blank">SCP-0000-EX</a> - An Ode to The Forgotten - [+39]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;All Foundation files regarding &quot;The All-seeing Eye&quot; are to be limited access to the Overseer Council. All mentions of &quot;Project Immortality&quot; and other actions regarding inter-dimensional analyzing of deaths of alternate individuals are to be expunged from Foundation databases.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A rewrite of my first proper SCP ever, SCP-5555-EX. I wrote 0000-EX in approximately one day upon being hit with inspiration for a rewrite I've been meaning to do for a long time. Though I'm pretty happy with how this article has turned out, I am probably going to rewrite it for a third time. We'll see.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5936" target="_blank">SCP-5936</a> - Those That Do Not Wish To Be Forgotten - [+28]</span></h4>
<p>&quot;<em>To ensure personnel safety following Event 5936-1, upon entering SCP-5936, all individuals are to thaumaturgically protect themselves by saying the following phrase loudly and clearly: <tt>&quot;I am me. My body is mine and mine only.&quot;</tt> All personnel failing to do so are to leave the entry point under the threat of immediate termination.</em>&quot;</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The first installment of the Ontokinetics Saga. I started writing this after me and my mother were riding through a section of our town that was totally abandoned - the buildings were almost intact, yet not a single human being could be found there. Additionally, the whole place was covered in fog, which only added to the already existing spookiness of it. My imagination did the rest of course, with me quickly tying the idea to an overarching narrative I had in my mind for quite some time, and thus SCP-5936 was born.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-0110-j" target="_blank">SCP-0110-J</a> - Personal Retirement, Effective Immediately - [+73]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;SCP-0110-J is an anomalous relationship between the number of Object Classes within the SCP Foundation's database and the number of months until an inevitable ÓK-Universe Collapse Scenario. The event has been noted to inevitably occur on 09/09/2030 within all observable multiverses.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A long time ago I said on SCPD that if <a href="/scp-5464">SCP-5464</a> somehow reaches +100, I will write something whilst drunk, similarly to what <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609776161" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;">PeppersGhost</a></span> did with <a href="/scp-3943">SCP-3943</a> after winning the SCP-4000 Contest. People only encouraged me of course. However, since I had no such beverages at my disposal, I thought that sleep deprivation is a good substitute. This is the product of that challenge.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5890" target="_blank">SCP-5890</a> - Within The Inner Prisons We Ourselves Made - [+25]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;The knowledge of the 1984-FALL Incident is to be limited to Foundation personnel of Clearance Level 3 or higher - all other individuals, including the entirety of the population of the Eastern regions of Poland, are to be administered amnestics.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This article is a rewrite of a very old draft of mine modified to fir both my current standards and the storyline already established in <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5936" target="_blank">SCP-5936</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/critter-profile-sparky" target="_blank">Critter Profile: Sparky!</a>. I had tons of fun writing this one, and I'm very happy with the end result. I think it's obvious by now, but I love serialized narratives strung out in-between different articles.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/the-watchman" target="_blank">The Watchman</a> - [+53]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;Jon Corderoy wasn't a good person. Long ago, he did unspeakable things. He stole, murdered, and abused the corrupt systems he lived in. Even after the end of the world, nothing changed. He still was the same piece of shit he had always been. If he was honest though, he didn't care.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Whilst before The Watchman I did attempt to write an article once<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-5" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-5')">5</a></sup>, this was my first successful one. As I had no idea what I was doing back in the day, I coldposted it, and surprisingly enough, it survived, and currently sits at a pretty nice number of upvotes. The whole idea and layout for the article pretty much popped into my mind during a walk near a sea and I wrote the whole thing in approximately 30 minutes. It's still, to this day, one of my favorite works of mine.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/the-overseer" target="_blank">The Overseer</a> - [+14]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;Well, let's start from the beginning - the end of the world happened. It wasn't like everyone always thought it would be - there were no explosions and there were no reality failures. No one expected that probably the most generic thing they contained would be their undoing.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The second installment in my short &quot;series&quot; centered around the world of the <a href="/revised-entry">Revised Entry</a> of SCP-173. Though looking back, it's pretty mediocre, I still like it quite the bit - especially considering that this was the first article my author avatar, Daniel Asheworth, appeared in.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/to-simply-be-loved" target="_blank">To Simply Be Loved</a> - [+30]</span></h4>
<p>(My 2020 Art Exchange gift to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/general-goose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6534493); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6534493&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610162460" alt="General Goose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6534493)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/general-goose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6534493); return false;">General Goose</a></span>)</p>
<p><em>&quot;Before there was time, before there was anything, there was nothing. And before there was nothing, there was an emotion. An emotion instilled, an emotion of pure creation, an emotion of beginnings and ends, an emotion of sadness and happiness, an emotion of compassion and hatred. This emotion was love.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I've had a ton of fun writing this one. I think I wrote it exactly one day after getting the info about my recipient - from doing the art to the writing, it was an absolute blast. Hopefully <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/general-goose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6534493); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6534493&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609776161" alt="General Goose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6534493)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/general-goose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6534493); return false;">General Goose</a></span> has as much fun reading it as I had creating it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/halfway-found-halfway-lost" target="_blank">Halfway Found, Halfway Lost</a> - [+16]</span></h4>
<p><em>&quot;Though the general consensus was that leaving work in the Foundation for later was rarely a good idea, James Micheals decided he was done for today; staying in the research lab for longer than ten hours would most likely result in permanent brain damage sooner or later. After all, it's not like staying here would make any sort of difference; the Department of Analitycs wouldn't just magically finish their work faster with one more useless person looking hanging about.&quot;</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The fourth installment in the Ontokinetics Saga and my first long tale. Writing it was fun, though somewhat hard since I had never really written anything like it before.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div></div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<h4><span>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/critter-profile-sparky" target="_blank">Critter Profile: Sparky!</a> - [+86]</span></h4>
<p>(A collaborative effort between myself and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610162460" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;">Uncle Nicolini</a></span>)</p>
<p><em>&quot;Sparky is a pretty sleepy fella (which is pretty ironic, considering his name) who likes to snooze for most of the day in his comfy pen. Once in a while he peeks through its doors and wags his tail at us; he's just so friendly to us caretakers! Hopefully, with the help of our therapy animals, we will be able to show Sparky that not all critters are bad!&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Author&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My first attempt at GOI Format, first collab, and first not-authored-by-myself article featuring Daniel Asheworth, my main character. This one was really, really fun to write. Probably the most fun I've had writing in a very long time.<br />
Halfway through the writing process <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609776161" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;">Uncle Nicolini</a></span> came and said &quot;okay, let me make this good&quot;, and that's pretty much what happened. I'm really grateful for his help, as he influenced the final shape of the article by a very long shot. This one's probably my favorite article I've written onsite.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
